The purpose of this is to minimize the amount of extraneous diffs that show up when making changes to the existing codebase.

# Eclipse IDE:
Code can be formatted by (CTRL-SHIFT-F). Imports can be organized by (CTRL-SHIFT-O).

## Installation Steps:
* Import code formatter:
** Open "Window->Preferences"
** Select "Java->Code Style->Formatter"
** Click "Import..."
** Browse to eclipse-java-freecharge-style.xml
** Click "Open" and "OK"
* Import "Organize Import" order:
** Open "Window->Preferences"
** Select "Java->Code Style->Organize Imports"
** Click "Import..."
** Browse to org.eclipse.jdt.ui.prefs
** Click "Open" and "OK"
* Configure "Save Actions":
** Open "Window->Preferences"
** Select "Java->Editor->Save Actions"
** Check "Perform the selected actions on save"
** Uncheck "Format source code"
** Uncheck "Organize imports"
** Check "Additional actions"
** Click "Configure..."
** Under "Code Organizing->Formatter", check "Remove trailing whitespace" and select "All lines"
** Uncheck all other "Save actions"
** Click "OK"
** "Additional Actions" should only show one bullet "Remove trailing white space on all lines"
** Click "OK"

# Intellij IDEA IDE (Preferable IDE):

## Installation Steps:
* Install Plugin:
** Settings (CTRL-ALT-S)
** Under IDE Settings, select "Plugins"
** Select the Available Tab
** Type "Eclipse" in the search bar
** Right-Click on Eclipse Code Formatter and choose "Download and Install"
** Select OK and restart IDEA
* Configure Plugin:
** Settings (CTRL-ALT-S)
** Under Project Settings, select "Eclipse Code Formatter"
** Select "Use the Eclipse Formatter"
** Check the box for "Enable Java"
** Uncheck the box for "Enable JavaScript"
** For "Eclipse Java Formatter config file", browse to eclipse-java-freecharge-style.xml
** Check the box for "Optimize Imports"
** For "Import Order", select "From File" and browse to org.eclipse.jdt.ui.prefs
** Select "Do not format other file types by IntelliJ formatter"
** Click OK.
* Disable the built-in import cleanups
** Settings (CTRL-ALT-S)
** Under Project Settings, select "Code Style", "Java", then "Imports"
** Change "Class count to use import with '*'" to 99
** Change "Names count to use static import with '*'" to 99
* Configure Editor
** Settings (CTRL-ALT-S)
** Under "IDE Settings", select "Editor"
** Check the box for "Enable in place Refactorings"
** For "Strip trailing spaces on Save", select "All"
** Under "IDE Settings/Editor", select "Auto Import"
** Uncheck the box for "Optimize imports on the fly"
** Under "IDE Settings/Editor", select "Appearance"
** Check the box for "Show line numbers" and method separators". See snapshot.
** Under "IDE Settings/Editor", select "Code Style"
** Check the box for "Enable formatter markers in comments". See snapshot.
* Configure Appearance & Behaviour
** Check the box for "Show memory indicator"
